---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL, SITE_NAME, SITE_URL } from '~/consts';
const lastUpdated = '2026-05-01';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description={`Terms under which you use ${SITE_NAME}: what the tool does, what it doesn't guarantee, and the usual liability limits.`}
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</em></p>

    <p>
      By using {SITE_NAME} (the "Service") at
      <a href={SITE_URL}>{SITE_URL}</a>, you agree to these Terms. If you do
      not agree, please do not use the Service.
    </p>

    <h2>1. The service</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE_NAME} provides a free web-based tool for rendering Mermaid
      diagrams from text, plus reference guides for the major diagram types.
      The tool runs inside your web browser and is offered "as is" and "as
      available".
    </p>

    <h2>2. Permitted use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You may use the Service for lawful personal, educational, or commercial purposes.</li>
      <li>
        You may not use the Service to process content whose processing would
        be illegal in your jurisdiction, including content that infringes
        others' intellectual property or privacy rights.
      </li>
      <li>
        You may not attempt to disrupt the Service — for example, by sending
        automated requests at a rate designed to degrade availability, or by
        probing for vulnerabilities without prior written permission.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Your content</h2>
    <p>
      The diagrams you paste, upload, or otherwise provide to the Service
      remain yours. In the current release, your diagrams are processed
      locally in your browser and are not transmitted to our servers. If a
      future feature requires a server upload, it will be clearly marked and
      will require your explicit action.
    </p>

    <h2>4. No warranty</h2>
    <p>
      The Service is provided without warranty of any kind, express or
      implied. The rendered diagram is produced by the Mermaid library and
      may differ from the rendering of the same source in another tool or
      Mermaid version. For production documentation, always re-render with
      the exact Mermaid version your destination platform uses.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the fullest extent permitted by law, {SITE_NAME} and its operator
      are not liable for any indirect, incidental, consequential, special, or
      punitive damages arising out of or related to your use of the Service,
      including but not limited to data loss, lost profits, or business
      interruption. Our aggregate liability to you for any claim arising out
      of the Service is limited to USD 0 (the Service is free).
    </p>

    <h2>6. Third-party links and ads</h2>
    <p>
      The Service may display advertisements served by Google AdSense and
      may link to third-party websites, including the Mermaid project's
      documentation. We are not responsible for the content, privacy
      practices, or availability of any third-party site or advertisement.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may modify these Terms as the Service evolves. The "Last updated"
      date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision. Your
      continued use of the Service after a change constitutes acceptance of
      the updated Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms are governed by the laws of the Republic of Korea, without
      regard to conflict-of-laws principles, to the extent that mandatory
      consumer protection laws of your place of residence do not provide
      otherwise.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these Terms can be sent to
      <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
